quran[12]{c,v,t,f}:
  16,106,"Whoever disbelieved in Allâh after his belief, except him who is forced thereto and whose heart is at rest with Faith; but such as open their breasts to disbelief, on them is wrath from Allâh, and theirs will be a great torment."
  16,107,"That is because they loved and preferred the life of this world over that of the Hereafter. And Allâh guides not the people who disbelieve."
  16,108,"They are those upon whose hearts, hearing (ears) and sight (eyes) Allâh has set a seal. And they are the heedless!"
  17,73,"Verily, they were about to tempt you away from that which We have revealed (the Qur’ân) unto you (O Muhammad صلى الله عليه و سلم), to fabricate something other than it against Us, and then they would certainly have taken you a Khalîl (an intimate friend)!"
  17,74,"And had We not made you stand firm, you would nearly have inclined to them a little."
  17,75,"In that case We would have made you taste a double portion (of punishment) in this life and a double portion (of punishment) after death. And then you would have found none to help you against Us."
  18,40,""
  18,41,""
  18,42,"So his fruits were encircled (with ruin). And he remained clapping his hands (with sorrow) over what he had spent upon it, while it was all destroyed on its trellises, and he could only say: "
  19,1,"Kâf-Hâ-Yâ-‘Aîn-Sâd. [These letters are one of the miracles of the Qur’ân, and none but Allâh (Alone) knows their meanings]."
  19,2,"(This is) a mention of the mercy of your Lord to His slave Zakariyyâ (Zachariah)."
  19,3,"When he called out his Lord (Allâh) a call in secret."